    <div class="mdl-card__supporting-text">
      <p>
        The offical Egee.io Rust server is a modded server and is moderated by Egee.io community member <i>GhostSquad57</i>.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Rust server uses Oxide and we use the following plugins:
      </p>
      <p>
        • <a href="http://oxidemod.org/plugins/rust-io-clans.842/">Rust:IO Clans</a><br>
        • <a href="http://oxidemod.org/plugins/gather-manager.675/">Gather Manager</a> (x3 gather rate)<br>
        • <a href="http://oxidemod.org/plugins/kits.668/">Kits</a><br>
        • <a href="http://oxidemod.org/plugins/n-teleportation.1832/">Teleportation</a> (Including homes & towns)<br>
        • <a href="http://oxidemod.org/plugins/stack-size-controller.1185/">Stack Size Controller</a><br>
      </p>
      <p>
        If you just want to check out the server map and see who's been playing, you can look at the <a href="http://playrust.io/#egee.io">live map</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Connecting to the Egee.io Rust server is simple:<br>
        &#8226; Fire up Rust<br>
        &#8226; From the main menu, click the "Play Game" icon<br>
        &#8226; Click "Modded" from the selections on the left side of the screen<br>
        &#8226; Enter <i>Egee</i> into the search field at the bottom of the screen<br>
        &#8226; Click the Egee.io server name in the server list and click "JOIN SERVER"<br>
      </p>
      <p>
        And that's it!
      </p>
